    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a quintessential analog performance machine. At its heart is the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been professionally serviced. Power is routed through a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock, ensuring exceptional traction and mid-corner adjustability. The chassis has been addressed for longevity with documented subframe reinforcement, a critical upgrade for this platform. The suspension remains taut with refreshed bushings and dampers, providing the precise turn-in and feedback expected of the M-division. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina consistent with a well-maintained driver, the powertrain and drivetrain are in excellent health, offering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline experience.",
